<subSubSection id="B6DC9EABFFF1FFABFCB474EEDCABFD02" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF1FFABFCB474EEDCABFD02" blockId="64.[831,1437,457,641]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFCB474EEDBD6FE62" bold="true" box="[831,942,457,481]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Comment</emphasis>
: The previously known distribution was confined to three localities 
<collectingRegion id="3C0203C2FFF1FFABFBD574CDDCCCFD82" box="[1118,1204,490,513]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
; for a map see 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFF1FFABFAC674CEDBECFDA2" author="ASSING, V." pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="243 - 262" refId="ref76746" refString="ASSING, V. 2015 c: New species and additional records of Lomechusini from the Palaearctic region, primarily from China (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 65 (2): 243 - 262." type="journal article" year="2015">ASSING (2015c)</bibRefCitation>
. The above material represents the first record from 
<collectingRegion id="3C0203C2FFF1FFABFC0B770EDBA0FDC2" box="[896,984,553,577]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
. The external and sexual characters are illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFF1FFABFC41776EDC0BFDE2" author="ASSING, V." box="[970,1139,585,609]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="243 - 262" refId="ref76746" refString="ASSING, V. 2015 c: New species and additional records of Lomechusini from the Palaearctic region, primarily from China (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 65 (2): 243 - 262." type="journal article" year="2015">ASSING (2015c)</bibRefCitation>
. Remarkably, all 
<specimenCount id="E8C006A9FFF1FFABFAA8776EDB00FD02" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
were collected from pig carrion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
